# {{ project_title }}

{{ project_description }}

Generated by [forge](https://github.com/cchifor/forge) with the **`worker`**
backend application template — a self-contained Python background-worker
service. It runs an async poll → handle → sleep loop instead of an HTTP
server, so there are no CRUD routes.

## Layout

```
src/worker/
  config.py         # environment-driven settings (pydantic-settings)
  observability.py  # structured logging + OpenTelemetry tracer
  worker.py         # the async worker loop (run / handle_iteration)
  __main__.py       # python -m worker
```

## Run

```bash
uv sync
uv run python -m worker
```

Configure via environment variables (prefix `WORKER_`):

| Variable                       | Default          | Meaning                              |
| ------------------------------ | ---------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `WORKER_SERVICE_NAME`          | `{{ project_slug }}` | name in logs / telemetry         |
| `WORKER_LOG_LEVEL`             | `INFO`           | logging level                        |
| `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS` | `5.0`            | sleep between iterations             |
| `WORKER_MAX_ITERATIONS`        | `0`              | stop after N iterations (`0` = forever) |

## Where to start

Replace `handle_iteration` in `src/worker/worker.py` with your real unit of
work — drain a queue, poll an upstream API, run a scheduled batch.

## Test

```bash
uv run pytest
```
